begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves. Evan has Cerebral Palsy. he wanted me not to worry if he raised his hand as it is a primarily not under his control thing that happens. I assured him that I know a man with CP and have known him since he was a kid, as he is my oldest child's best friend and has been since middle school. Evan has 7 siblings, he lives in Idaho, about a half hour from Boise.
middle_memory_text: Evan is making a podcast where he imagines that he has started a new radio station, and he is working on it from the ground up. So some parts are what is happening wit the imaginary radio station and some parts are just programming, but even these include a lot of creative content as he is making up radio commercials for his radio shows.
end_memory_text: His family and my family have both been meeting online in Zoom meetings. It is coincidentally something both families started as a way to keep in contact during the Pandemic. For me, we have been much closer than we otherwise were.Even's family and my family (equally large, I have 7 siblings as well, but grew up with 8) are both spread out among the US. But he also has a sister who currently lives in Jordan. Her husband is in the diplomatic corps and they live at the US Embassy.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of this week I have very little planned. I will probably do some laundry and change my bedding. I do have a Chiropractic appointment tomorrow. next Monday I have a hearing test and my initial appointment with a new ENT doctor referred to by my primary care doctor. So I will get to see if there is anything he wants to try to help with my tinnitus. Also on Monday is report day for Unemployment. So I will get to see is I qualify for the federal extension on unemployment or just the state. The state was 20 weeks, they extended to 26 weeks, and I have received 26 weeks. The US government has extended benefits to 57 weeks, and while I receive PUI, the federal benefits, rather than the state benefits (I was only part time and did not make enough to qualify) from what I have read, I will not get extended because I was part time. I will continue to report just in case they change their minds on that or add additional benefits again.
critical_positive: We were both willing to talk about ourselves. We both tried to find subjects that we could both talk about. While we had little in common, we worked those things in common to create a conversation, and that lead to other topics that allowed for a wide varied conversation. We encouraged each other.
critical_negative: Evan was a little late to the conversation, and I had just checked the time and was about to stop waiting when he arrived. He blamed it on technical difficulties. He is a big sports fan. I am not. But he did mention hockey, and I have learned how to make a little conversation with hockey fans. We have little in common, but that just makes it a little harder.
employ_7_TEXT: Disabled, but I was working part time as an essential worker, but took a leave of absence when I read that hypertension makes me more vulnerable to Covid19. My employer continued to pay for my dental insurance for 2 and a half months before they terminated my employment. I will resume working when it is safe to do so.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where each other was from, how many siblings the other person had and we talked about the fact that we were both disabled.
middle_memory_text: To be honest the conversation went all over the place. He did most of the talking and was talking about everything from Gordie Howe, the famous Detroit Red Wings hockey player, to the automobile Museum in Detroit, to the material they use on aircraft carriers, and even a little bit about politics. Like I said, the conversation went everywhere and was difficult to follow at times.
end_memory_text: Towards the end of the conversation we discussed how many times we have taken part in this study and the kinds of people we have been talking to. Honestly, he wanted to keep the conversation going and I had other obligations and I was not able to stay on the conversation an unlimited length of time.
rest_of_day_open: I don't see myself having a lot to do this week. This can be a good thing and a bad thing because when I have nothing to do I get depressed very easily and start having negative thoughts. However, it can also be very nice because I don't feel a lot of pressure to get anything done.
critical_positive: We certainly did not have the lack of conversational topics to discuss. He seemed very outgoing and able to keep the conversation going easily. Also, I was a little bit late to the conversation and so he was able to stick around and wait for a few minutes for the conversation to start which was very helpful for me.
critical_negative: As I'm sure the video of the conversation will reflect, the conversation was very one-sided. I didn't say much at all and even when I did say something sometimes he would even cut me off and continue with what he was saying. Honestly, that is partially the reason why I did not want the conversation to go much further because I had no idea how long I would be there if it did.
